Step 1. Compute the Debt to Equity Ratio.  
 • From the balance sheet, the Total Current Liabilities at period end = 631,880.98  
 • The Total Owner’s Equity at period end = 14,167,783.63  
 • Debt to Equity Ratio = 631,880.98 / 14,167,783.63 ≈ 0.0446, which rounds to 0.04  

Step 2. Compute the Net Profit Margin.  
 • From the income statement, Net Profit = 1,167,783.63 and Total Revenue = 3,397,619.40  
 • Net Profit Margin = (1,167,783.63 / 3,397,619.40) × 100 ≈ 34.38%  

Step 3. Compute the Return on Assets (ROA).  
 • From the balance sheet, Total Assets at period end = 14,799,664.61  
 • ROA = (Net Profit / Total Assets) × 100 = (1,167,783.63 / 14,799,664.61) × 100 ≈ 7.88%  

Step 4. Compute the Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio.  
 • Accounts Receivable (AR) values: initial = 0.00, end = 2,902,136.39;  
 • Average AR = (0.00 + 2,902,136.39) / 2 = 1,451,068.195  
 • Main Business Revenue = 3,397,619.40  
 • Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio = 3,397,619.40 / 1,451,068.195 ≈ 2.34  

Thus, the solution is:  
{
  "solution": {
    "Debt to Equity Ratio": "0.04",
    "Net Profit Margin": "34.38%",
    "Return on Assets (ROA)": "7.88%",
    "Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio": "2.34"
  }
}
